translated: Jongchell, Arvid, PhD, Customs Control Officer, Gothenburg, b. 12/1/84 in Nårunga, Älvsborg county. Bachelor's degree from Gothenburg High Latin School in 1905, Bachelor of Arts from Gothenburg University in 1911, licentiate degree in 1927 and earned PhD in 1931 from the same university. He has studied in Germany, France, Belgium, Netherlands, Denmark, Norway, England, Italy, Czechoslovakia, Poland, Hungary, Switzerland and Austria. He began working as a clerk in customs in 1905, became a clerk in succession at the Gothenburg Customs Inspectorate in 1912, deputy clerk in 1912, and then a customs officer in Gothenburg in 1930. He was appointed head of the customs inspection sample proofing in Gothenburg from 1937 to 1942, head of the postal customs department since 1944, chief customs officer at the central customs chamber in Gothenburg since 1945, and customs supervisor in Gothenburg since 1946. He was invited to assist the General Customs Board in developing the merchandise manual for the 1929 customs tariff. He was a member of the Philological Society at Gothenburg University, the 1884 Men's Society, treasurer and secretary of Gothenburg's local branch of the Swedish General Customs Officers' Association for several years, chairman of that local branch from 1931 to 1934, and a member of the national board of the General Swedish Customs Officers' Association from 1931 to 1934. His publications include: "Huo Kuang and his Time. Extracts from Pan Ku's Ch'ien Han Shu", thesis in Sinology in 1930, literary articles in Gothenburg Aftonbladet from 1908 to 1911, minor articles in notices from the Customs Agency, Linggymnasium Anniversary Papers, Swedish Gardening Magazine, Customs IF Anniversary Papers, and People's School Reading Books. His hobby is tree cultivation, especially sports and game park landscaping. Married.
